Minister of state for Budget and National Planning, Prince Clem Ikanade Agba on Wednesday spoke of  President Muhammadu Buhari’s commitment to cushioning the hardship the citizens of the Country are facing.  Oba Ewuare II said that the president had heard the demands of the youths and he would act on them accordingly.  He said that the youths had no other countries they could call their own, and advised them not to have it destroyed by “their own actions and on that, they should give peace a chance.” The royal father further commiserated with those who lost their loved ones during the crisis. He thanked the president for approving the construction of railway line that would pass through the Benin axis.